The paper proposes a novel policy search algorithm for reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The algorithm is tested on continuous control tasks, which are typically studied in robotics and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also mentions the use of deep policies, which suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the algorithm involves both online and offline optimization, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
